             <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC"><!--update lang and resp here-->              
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><w type="formula" lemma="maqqas">ᚋᚐᚊᚔ</w> <name nymRef="#?">ᚅᚔᚂᚔ</name></persName>
                </ab> 
            </div>                    
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" xml:space="preserve" resp="#POC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up"/><persName><w type="formula" lemma="maqqas">MAQI</w> <name nymRef="#?">NILI</name></persName>
                </ab>
               <!-- <ab type="list"></ab>-->
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                <app n="1">
<note>Macalister's (1916, 231) reading NILI is clearly correct.</note>                    
                </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>'of the son of Nilos?'</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                 <p>Although the inscription reads NILI, a spelling of NELI would be expected instead (nom. *<distinct xml:lang="sga">Néll</distinct>, Mod. Ir. <distinct xml:lang="ga">Níall</distinct>). </p>
            </div>
